The paper deals with optimization problems involving submodular functions, which are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of entropy in the objective function suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The application of the problem to fairness in cooperative games suggests a connection to game theory (cs.GT). The use of biased network flows in the analysis suggests a connection to theoretical computer science and algorithms (cs.LG). Finally, the problem can also be seen as a variant of the minimum spanning tree problem, which falls under the subfield of computational geometry and topology (cs.SI).
